summary: SummaryThe MAC Hyper Real Serumizer Eye Treatment is a radiance-boosting eye treatment that delivers a -32%* visible reduction in 360° dark circles in just 12 weeks - and smooths, tightens and repairs the skin barrier. *Clinical testing on 45 panelists after 12 weeks of use, twice a day.
details: DetailsResearch ResultsAfter 12 weeks: -32% reduction in appearance of 360° dark circles*After 12 weeks: -20% reduction in appearance of undereye puffiness**Immediate: +94% improvement in hydration****Clinical testing on 45 panelists after 12 weeks of use, twice a day.**Clinical testing on 33 panelists after 12 weeks of use, twice a day.***Clinical testing on 23 panelists after one use.Key IngredientsJapanese Peony ExtractVitamin CNiacinamideCeramidesItem 2636002How To UseApply twice a day, morning and evening, as part of your Hyper Real™ skincare routine. Dispense one pump directly onto a fingertip and gently tap around the contour of one eye. With gentle pressure, sweep your fingertip from the inner corner to outer corner underneath the eye. Continue massaging upward to the lid and brow bone, then back to the inner corner to ensure 360° application around the entire eye area. Repeat on the other eye.IngredientsWater\Aqua\Eau, Glycerin, Dimethicone, Butylene Glycol, Isohexadecane, Octyldodecanol, Alcohol Denat., Squalane, Glyceryl Stearate, Peg-100 Stearate, Sodium Polyaspartate, Niacinamide, Algae Extract, Paeoniaalbiflora Flower Extract, Caffeine, Trametes Versicolor Extract, Ascorbyl Glucoside, Acetyl Hexapeptide-8, Trehalose, Holesterol, Linoleic Acid, Sorbitol, Aleurites Moluccanus Seed Oil, Mangifera Indica (Mango) Seed Butter, Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter, Polybutene, Whey Protein\Lactis Protein\Protéine Du Petit-Lait, Ceramide Ng, Dimethiconol, Dipotassium Glycyrrhizate, Laminaria Digitata Extract, Beeswax\Cera Alba\Cire D'abeille, Sodium Hyaluronate, Caprylyl Glycol, Thylhexylglycerin, Silica, Citric Acid, Polyacrylate Crosspolymer-6, Hdi/Trimethylol Hexyllactone Crosspolymer, Cetyl Alcohol, Behenyl Alcohol, Oleic/Linoleic/Linolenic Polyglycerides, Hydroxyethyl Acrylate/Sodium Acryloyldimethyl Taurate Copolymer, Hydrogenated Lecithin, Sodium Hydroxide, Sodium Phytate, Polysorbate 60, Sorbitan Isostearate, Disodium Edta, Tocopheryl Acetate, Hydroxyacetophenone, Tetrahexyldecyl Ascorbate, Tocopherol, Phenoxyethanol, Potassium Sorbate.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

faceoff_positive.comments:
As someone who's struggled with hereditary dark circles, I've tried numerous eye creams in search of the perfect one. I was excited to see MAC added the Serumizer Eye to their Hyper Real collection, a line I already love. 

Over the past two weeks, I've used this product twice daily as the last step in my skincare routine, distributing a pea-sized amount between each ring finger and gently patting it around my entire eyes.

The texture is more like a gel than a cream, super lightweight and absorbs quickly without leaving any greasiness or residue. It instantly hydrates and plumps my fine lines, leaving the skin around my eyes looking refreshed and radiant. 

I wait a few minutes before applying makeup to ensure the product is fully absorbed to avoid any patchiness. One of my favorite things about this product is how beautifully it pairs with my makeup. I typically use a color corrector, concealer, and powder to cover my dark circles, but these products can sometimes accentuate fine lines and make my under-eyes appear cakey. When I use Serumizer, my products blend seamlessly, giving my under-eyes a more natural, skin-like appearance.

While I'll need more time to assess the product's long-term effectiveness in reducing my dark circles, I've already noticed an improvement. The skin around my eyes appears tighter, and my dark circles are less prominent. Although I may never find a miracle product that magically erases my dark circles, Serumizer delivers noticeable results. My eyes look healthier, more youthful, and the way my concealer applies on top is enough to make this product a holy grail for me.
faceoff_positive.headline: My new holy grail

faceoff_negative.comments: I've been using this serumizer twice daily for almost two weeks, and my experience has been mixed. I haven't noticed a significant difference in reducing dark circles or brightening, but I have seen improvements in other areas. It's lightweight, fast absorbing, and hydrated the skin well. One of the benefits has been how well it works under makeup. My concealer now applies more smoothly and doesn't crease, which used to be an issue. However, I've experienced sensitivity when applying it under my eyes. It makes my eyes feel irritated, like I need to blink more often, though this is less noticeable at night. On the plus side, it's fragrance free, easy to use, and dries quickly. If dark circles are your main concern, this might not be the solution. But if you're looking for a hydrating eye treatment that improves the application of makeup and smooths the under eye area, this product does deliver. I received this product for free from Topbox Marketing for testing and reviewing purposes.
faceoff_negative.headline: Hydrating and Makeup Friendly, But Not a Dark Circle Fix
